      <h2>IssueSeverity</h2>
      <p>How the issue affects the success of the action.</p>
      <p>This value set has an inline code system http://hl7.org/fhir/issue-severity, which defines the following codes:</p>
      <table class="codes">
        <tr>
          <td>
            <b>Code</b>
          </td>
          <td>
            <b>Display</b>
          </td>
          <td>
            <b>Definition</b>
          </td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>fatal
            <a name="fatal"> </a>
          </td>
          <td>Fatal</td>
          <td>The issue caused the action to fail, and no further checking could be performed.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>error
            <a name="error"> </a>
          </td>
          <td>Error</td>
          <td>The issue is sufficiently important to cause the action to fail.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>warning
            <a name="warning"> </a>
          </td>
          <td>Warning</td>
          <td>The issue is not important enough to cause the action to fail, but may cause it to be performed suboptimally or in a way that is not as desired.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>information
            <a name="information"> </a>
          </td>
          <td>Information</td>
          <td>The issue has no relation to the degree of success of the action.</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>
